C:\Users\sarah\Desktop\Udemy\PerlCourse>perl tut8b.pl green eggs


to install a package do a search on perl from start menu and select package manager.  

to use command prompt perl change environmental variable C:\cygwin64\bin (if that is where it is).  type perl -v to see if that took

name your file filename.pl and then at the prompt type perl filename.pls

OR...   you can install gitbash and have a linuxish system.  type perl filename.pl
